@1:50 I think you need to look again, that is not turning at 8:1 ratio, you says "8 turns of that is one turn of that" whilst showing the disc turning several times and the opposite disc only turning by 1 "notch" which would be backwards, when you did it the other way around, same effect. Not only that but this is not gearing anything because you're loosing speed AND torque which is not a gearset, you're dumping/dampening in the input force. 

IF this was working you should be able to show side A moving 8x slower in relation to side B with 8x the amount of torque and in reverse side B moving 8x running 8x faster with 8x less torque being transmitted.

I think you need to rethink this because it appears you are getting a major transmission loss in both direction. Also, how much actual power are you able to transmit through it? I don't think this is useful for anything than a massive energy sink.

